b'' b'text b'' b'bhogaisvarya-prasaktanam' b'tayapahrta-cetasam' b'vyavasayatmika buddhih' b'samadhau na vidhiyate' b'' b'bhoga--to material enjoyment; aisvarya--and opulence; prasaktanam--for' b'those who are attached; taya--by such things;' b'apahrta-cetasam--bewildered in mind; vyavasaya-atmika--fixed in' b'determination; buddhih--devotional service to the lord; samadhau--in' b'the controlled mind; na--never; vidhiyate--does take place.' b'' b'translation' b'' b'in the minds of those who are too attached to sense enjoyment and' b'material opulence, and who are bewildered by such things, the resolute' b'determination for devotional service to the supreme lord does not take' b'place.' b'' b'purport' b'' b"samadhi means ``fixed mind.'' the vedic dictionary, the nirukti," b"says, samyag adhiyate 'sminn atma-tattva-yathatmyam: ``when the mind is" b"fixed for understanding the self, it is said to be in samadhi.''" b'samadhi is never possible for persons interested in material sense' b'enjoyment, nor for those who are bewildered by such temporary things.' b'they are more or less condemned by the process of material energy.' b'' b'bhagavad-gita as it is' b'books of a.c. bhaktivedanta swami' b'' b'' b'---------------------------------------------------------' b"| don't forget to chant: b'| b'| hare krishna hare krishna, krishna krishna hare hare b'| hare rama hare rama, rama rama hare hare b'| b"| kalki's infoline bbs aiken, south carolina, usa b'---------------------------------------------------------' 